§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A function $f: 𝗥^n → 𝗥^m$ is ❬linear❭ if
    𝍫 ⦊
      ‣ $f(x + y) = f(x) + f(y)$ for all $x, y ∈ 𝗥^n$, and ⦉

      ‣ $f(αx) = αf(x)$ for all $α ∈ 𝗥$ and $x ∈ 𝗥^n$. ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ Equivalently, $f(αx + βy) = αf(x) + βf(y)$ for all $α, β
    ∈ 𝗥$ and $x, y ∈ 𝗥^n$. ⦉

  ‖ In this case, we say that ❬superposition❭ holds. ⦉
⦉

